The paper focuses on improving the performance of deep speaker embedding models for speaker verification, which involves speech processing and machine learning techniques. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.SD (Sound). Additionally, the paper proposes a hybrid neural network structure and a regularization scheme, which are related to deep learning and optimization, respectively. Thus, cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) are also likely sub-categories. The paper also evaluates its proposed method on the NIST SRE 2016 and 2018 datasets, which are commonly used for speaker verification research. Therefore, cs.SI (Sound and Image Processing) is another possible sub-category. Finally, since the paper proposes improvements to an existing model, it could also be classified under cs.SD (Software Development).
